-- Louisville Tops Colorado State to Reach NCAA Regional Semifinals
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2013-03-23T23:41:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-23/louisville-tops-colorado-state-to-reach-ncaa-regional-semifinals.html
The University of Louisville, the
No. 1 seed in the Midwest region, defeated Colorado State
University 82-56 to reach the regional semifinals of the
national men’s college basketball tournament.  Russ Smith scored 27 points for the Cardinals (31-5) and
Gorqui Dieng added 12 at Rupp Arena in Lexington, Kentucky.  Greg Smith  scored 14 and Daniel Bejarano had 10 for the
eighth-seeded Rams (26-9), who trailed 45-31 at the half.  Louisville will play the winner of the game between Oregon
and  Saint Louis  in the National Collegiate Athletic Association
Tournament’s regional semifinal.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nancy Kercheval at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net  